Here are both approaches using Shell navigation and `IQueryAttributable`.

**1. Route registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)**
```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigation from ProductListPage (code-behind or VM)**
```csharp
// Approach A: pass the ID as a simple string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?ProductId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: pass the full object via a dictionary
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage),
    new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        ["Product"] = selectedProduct   // complex object
    });
```

**3. ViewModel receiving both — `IQueryAttributable`**
```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    // Single entry point for ALL query data
    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("ProductId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach B: full object passed via dictionary
        if (query.TryGetValue("Product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page**
```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param (`?key=val`) | Object param (dictionary) |
|---|---|---|
| **Types** | Strings only | Any object |
| **URL-safe** | Yes | No (not in the URI) |
| **Deep-link friendly** | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, flags | Full model, complex state |

Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` call, so you can support either navigation style from a single ViewModel.
